values:
I have been resistant to posting partly because words make things real. 

I am leaving the non-profit world to be a doula and a midwife wow! my heads spins at the thought and there are so many things i need to get in order its really mind boggling. Luckily my mother bought me a laptop which solves many of my problems and I just feel so overwhelmed by the move I am making. I have the support of my friends but I havent told my mother yet. I told my chritians godmother and she was like Oh. I expect my mother to freak out and make me freak out. when I am ready I may send a letter. I just dont want to fall off my cloud of faith because my mom is a mess. I just keep putting things off and putting one foot in front of the other. Whew! good times man good times.

No I am not joking. It got stolen sunday night and I noticed monday morning. So now I am trying to figure out how to get to all the places that a car would make easy and possible to get to. it sucks and I am still in shock by it but I am just hoppig that I get a car soon, even better than the one I had. I will keep all posted.

Man and lemme tell you Barney's burger makes it all better. I am eating a hikcory turkey burger and seasoned fries feeling the bad food course through my body on this beautiful sunshine day and I feel good. 

I decided to go ahead and buy my mother a vibrator for her 50th and if she goes off then imma just hafta deal with it. I think she will thank me later even if just silently. S

So this weekend Imm go visit Obatala cause well i am in need of his clarity, love and patience. Its been awhile since i have been to see him and I wonder what will come up. I keep seeing a white plate with 8 pears and cascarilla so that is what he will have and now it is in writing so yeah. 
ok this food is too good so ill be back with a real update peace.

I love it cause the day jus goes by so much faster. I mean awesome. So my job hunt continues and seeing that it took me 8 months last time, i am in chill mode about it right now and am hoping I will gone by june and in my new place by july. Oh speaking of which, I meditated this morning and decided to tell my landlord that I am moving out july 1st. This also means that my roomie needs to know that but that gives me and everyone eles plenty of time. I am hoping that my roomie can stay in that house and I get my full deposit with no bumps. I have been looking at the market and until I get a job that pays more it looks like I may end up in a studio, which is ok since I need to collect some things anyway so be prepared to get a invite to gift me house items cause imma need my community on this one. I must say the thought of living by myself is scary. There is so much that now lands on my back. Like: the rent, food, saftey, bills and more. I am also excited to have my own space and not have to hurt somebody because of them being asses, or dirty or disrespectful. I also look forward to a one bedroom since that is truly what I want. I am excited folks. 

Then on the job front, I am a bit afraid of making 46000-52000 just becasue the expectation goes up. I wonder where I will find that money and the job that makes me jump outta bed and rush to work, having fun all day. Man, I visualized this place and I will have it.

I have also decided to go on a silent retreat the summer regarless of if I have the vacation time or not. its 10 days long and all you do is eat, sleep, shit, piss and meditate. I know it will be difficult but I feel like there are lots of places in my spirit that need attention and healing and I want to give myself just that. We shall see.

Outside. the sky is clear as hell and I am feelin good. Whateva had me down has passed and I am not back in my element. I decided I was taking on too much of other people's stuff and have since made two appointments to get body work done instead of go to therapy. I am not sure for how long but I feel like it is what I need right now and then I will go back. I feel so clever to come up with that cause I can't afford therapy and body work so here I go man. Plus I am taking a human day off sunday. Saturday night imma take a whit bath, put on some white clothes and all sunday just relax and not talk to humans at all. No cellie on, just me, books and TV maybe a movie or two ya heard me. I am about feeding my spirit right now in any way I can cause the shit is gettin deep. I am about movin and shakin my world instead of waiting for shit to happen. I look forward to what is to come, to livin in my own place, to have a job I love and pays me my worth. I cant wait to receive olokun and allow him to change my life. and to see my eggun soon. I love you all.

i am veinte cinco or 25 in english. I kinda feel like i am in a daze about it. Like i was and am excited but i want more, like a parade. People screaming and dancing, celebrating that I was born and that I survived cause I really could be doing worse. I mean, I got the phone calls (which i intensly appreciate) and I am having a party but I mean my 24th was good but I was somewhere else so i kinda feel like i am celebrating my 24th, 25th, survival of my fire, rebirth of me trhough ocha. Also, I am like damn im 25 and I am trying to figure out what that means. You know like at 21 it was about getting laid and partying or 18 was about independence. I guess 25 is about putting it all together, creating the foundation for your adult life. Or maybe its that I am an adult but am not ready. who knows. either way time continues and I will only get older. I hope to enjoy this age/year and to appreciate this time. I hope to heal and get to know myself intimatly. I hope to find abundance, money, love and my dreams. I hope....

Abundance has/is my theme for 2007. and I would love to say not in that greedy way but it is definetly in that kid that wants more cookies when they have just hade like 9 and they need to share with the other kids. I am opening myself up to having more than what I need. My neccesities are taken care of, I get by. I want to not live pay check to pay check. I want to take vacations to places that are outside of CA shit outside the country. When I need something spritual I want money to not be the hinderence hell nothing to hinder it. I want to quit a job and not worry for 6 months, I want no debt I want freedom that can come from money. Yeah its a move away from the hardcore lefty I had become, but that was before bills started growing in the back yard screaming for more water when I was having a drought. I feel that it is possible I also feel that abundance of all kind (health, relationships, happiness, confidence and more) is possible and I will have these things because though I cant see it because It has never been in my life I can feel it down into my soul so much so that when I really let myself feel it I cry because I know.

With all that said i had a kick ass holiday. I was able to get my mother a present for x-mas. I enjoyed her company and I brought in the new year with a game of uno, good cheese, melissa and tracy. I spent my first day of the new year with orisha and it was beautiful. I am so blessed to be apart of a tradition/religion that allows me to touch God. I mean really sit on that y'all, its off da hook(understatment not intended but shit there are no words really).

I was thinking about the fact that a year ago today I had my fire and how far i have come. Thanks to eggun, orisha, my mother, my cousin, friends and myself I cam through well. It was hard and continues to be but it is really amazing how much it helped me to grow. I changed alot because of that experience and many others that came after. I really look forward to this year. Heres to new friendships to be made, old relationships that revolve and abundance. May this year bring you what you need and more.
Ache

Last night I went to Ameoba and was just kickin it by myself when I realized the plague that is early twenties has almost completly lifted. oh god it is so good. All that feeling of loneliness and that no one loves me including me. the fighting everyone and everything. not knowing myself one minute and then feeling like I have a grasp just to have pulled from underneath. I feel a weight has lifted off of me. I feel content and clear about how I want to reach my goals. I have not fought with my mom in awhile because i let shit go. I havent fought with many people in awhile. its hard for me to describe this feeling on paper (computer) but I love it. bottom line my future, my present feel clear and the fact that i dont fully understand it clear. oh the joy.

You are The Moon

Hope, expectation, Bright promises.

The Moon is a card of magic and mystery - when prominent you know that nothing is as it seems, particularly when it concerns relationships. All logic is thrown out the window.

The Moon is all about visions and illusions, madness, genius and poetry. This is a card that has to do with sleep, and so with both dreams and nightmares. It is a scary card in that it warns that there might be hidden enemies, tricks and falsehoods. But it should also be remembered that this is a card of great creativity, of powerful magic, primal feelings and intuition. You may be going through a time of emotional and mental trial; if you have any past mental problems, you must be vigilant in taking your medication but avoid drugs or alcohol, as abuse of either will cause them irreparable damage. This time however, can also result in great creativity, psychic powers, visions and insight. You can and should trust your intuition.

So I have a job y'all in da east bay and apart of me is excited but the other half of me is terrified. not about the job but my money situation. see i have none and my job doesn't start till 12/11 and in the meantime I have bills, lots of them. i am not sure where the money is going to come from but i also didn't know where my job was going to come from. of course i looked for my job for 5 months and i have only been looking for money for like 2 weeks but who know. so if you or some one you know is sitting on extra money of any ammount kick a sista down some i need like 2k to be aight which in the world id not that much. 
in other news

So that I can continuously get this feeling out of my body here I go. I am freaking out and not freaking out about my job situation which feels like only7 yeasterday that I was in the same situation. I keep thinking about how I was rescued but it was at the last possible momment and I was nervous until that momment and I am hoping that I can be saved way before the last possible momment cause I gots bills man lots of them ya heard me.so you, me and everyone within a 200 mile radius of me need to pray alot that I get a job, i get one that is the one i want/need that it pays much more than the one I have that I ge this job within the next month and it is a smooth transition. ok with all that said i am fundraising for a ceremony i need soon cause my stomach pains are coming back and I cant afford to go to the doctor where they will tell me they dont know whats wrong with me but I know so yeah. If ya got 5 bucks or 500 to kick my way please do so maybe I can make something for ya as a exchange (jordan). 
on another note I finally bought a dye and some soda ash so I can start dyeing fabric we shall see where that goes. ok i feel better now off to the races.

first off imma say this to the public...I am enjoying Kanye west. his music that is ok i have said it moving on.

This year has been a learning experience...why do i bring this up now, well because a long story short my care registration was late and I can't use my car that I am paying for till i go through hella hoops...Each time I tell someone about my trials of 2006 they are like yeah...ocha comin huh. yeah i know that you got the money for it cause I dont hell i still need an orisha and lords knows i dont have the money so.... I know a way will be made but untill then....wait a way is beginning to be made I mean my finances are in the balance and I am seeking another job which i feel is going welll....oh gawd the thought of not going to (well u know the place) makes me feel warm and fuzzy inside...like jordan feels when he thinks of leaving sf ( oh by the way good luck wit dat bro) whew, i have alot going on but i sit in this moment feeling good about it because it is the change i have been asking for for a long time. its hard and time consuming but watching me and life fall into the places i need feels soo goo and deserved

me against me (and maybe the world)

I had a dream I was a Iyawo...nuf said.
SO I am ok, I love my place and my roomie. Now if I could get the money thing down I'd be ok. I am excited about some upcoming ceremonies I need and will have before this year is out. Ummm other than that I have just been hella busy...with life and work. I need a momment to myself and I am going to get it one way or the other. Oh and there is a house party to come so stay tuned and keep your ears to the grind stone.

Yesterday i went to this celebration of for mi madre, Yemaya and It was off da hook. they did songd from brasil and cuba, dances and yea. i almost cried for so many reasons. it was the best i have felt in months. which brings me to my next point...  something is happening, i am coming to so many realizations about myself. i understand that all the things happened to me, for me so i can better understand myself and my pain. i am happy because i am healing... i have been for awhile but i thought it had to look a certain way and i now know that it should look exactly as it does. i have a long journey but i am on it not ready cause i am already here and now. i am being carried and assited to me if that makes sense. i don't like nor do i love myself but at the same time i do and i will. ashe.
erica aleyo omo yemaya y ochun

Hello Everyone,
So for those who may not know my home caught on fire on monday and it was a disaster. My house in inhabitable and I lost many items. The good news is that no one was home and therefore not hurt. I thaank you for your calls and support I need it now and will in the near future so keep the prayers, positive thoughts and calls coming.
Many of you requested a list of things I need so that if you had it, knew somwone that did, or could provide it you would. Thantk you for the offer and here is that list...

Mattress, box spring (full sized bed, if possible not too soft)
lap top
gift certificate to a book store (many of my book either burned or are smoke damaged)
cd holder (book looking kind)
photo abulms
dishes and utencils
glass bowl ( like a small fish bowl)
clothes
apartment (in oakland or berkeley around $400-500 prefer with POC/queer but doesn't have to be and near public trans)
storage containers
boom box
moving boxes
Sheets (full sized bed)
towels and wash clothes
tv
vcr
pillows
pots, pans, skillets

I believe that is all for now. Again thank you so much and even just your support and love will aid in caring me through this tough time and transition. I love you all and see you all soon.
Erica Newport 408-888-8198.

I keep this running fantasy in my head that some old whit lady finds out about my life and wants to help me so she gives me enough money to pay off my debt, retire my mom, buy her a new car, a new house, pay off the condo she has, tells me to quit my job, and then gives me money to live off of for the rest of my life and I  build a house where my broke friends can live and build my madrina a huge house and next to that a ocha house so hers is left as a home. then I go and stay in spain till I feel like coming back knowing spanish having met a guy named something awesome and he loves the ground i walk on and i get back to the us go to school get my phd, travel some more and then it fades to black cause I can't see past that point. then I wake up and see all of my bills that are stacked to the ceiling and over due, the immense amount of debt iam in, a job that i am ready to leave but need the money for and a mom that is so tired she can't sleep. But for just a little while i am swept off to a place where at least one part of my life is fixed like a broken drain and i am left with the hope that one day it will come true.

Welp, did what I had to so that I could get my warriors and yeah twas good. So I have been told that I should write my life down and I have had some false starts and for some reason I am getting the urge to try again. I have no idea really what this may or may not do for me but I figure why not.

well my mom got outta surgery ok thank lordisa and she is recovering quite well.
moving on...this week will be full but good. i am looking forward to each day this month because it is full of wonderful and exciting things. I got a knock in the stomach about grade school, but really i am probably justing playing head games with myself and will get over it. 
moving on...where this man is that eggun is sending me needs to show the hell up.
moving on....

well, things are bit less crazy, although my mom is completly freaking out about her surgery and I am just not. I did for a second and then I was like no my mom will be fine and she is not I will deal with that as it comes yes. I said my good byes to kristi who took me off of myspace setting the "battlelines" as jordan would say. I found it funny but a bit hurtful but considering the pain I have been feeling the last year it aint that bigga deal. I feel good about the decision and it made me go hey who else is holding me back. there are a few friendship imma let go and others imma reshape so that i can deal. i have met so many new and great people that i no longer have time to try and keep up with certain people. to think i was worried when i graduated that i wouldn't meet new people. I should have known i mean i am a social butterfly and i come from social butterflies. i mean at the end of the day i have to say mojucue to orisha, eggun and my godparents for hookin it up. and much love to my god brothers and sisters that are helping me figure out who i am and love myself as is. i have learned so much in the last year it is amazing and I am truely coming into myself. i am excited to get to know me and go on vacation hahahahah.
Didn't get called back for a second round but that means I can focus more on getting into grad school. let go grad school lets go *clap clap*

Well, I went to this beyond awesome women's retreat this weekend for work but also for me. I have never felt so supported and loved by strangers in my life. and this weekend further let me know how much i need female energy. I am forever changed by this weekend and I got pulled into a support group that was formed out of this weekend with a women I so want to continue to know. I met all these folks who knew madrina and they rocked and let me know even more that she rocks. I mean she was a fucking activist/lesbian/and aleyo when the shit was truely uncool. she has started things that i am just beginning to look into and lordisa help i am so glad she is my madrina. anyway, I let somethings go up at that ranch and gained wonderful  new people into my life i must go again and again and bring my mother. other than that i am just resting and trying to get things done fo real real not fo play play.

I need something and I know what ithink but when how not so sure . i think imma just sit in silence a bit more and uhhhh yeah.

well the top has blown on my life again. I knew it would cause well i just knew. it aint all bad I just know that this is happening cause i am cleansing and when i cleanse everything gets mixed up. olokun is bringing things to the surface so i must deal. plus yemaya and oya (well i am not sure) are just whipping my life into a frenzy. i am just trying to keep it all straight. working on ish with my mom, work, friends, finaces, spirit, living space, school blah blah. i know that it will all come together and i will look back like damn i went through all that. Since my misa i have been going far in and just doing alot of healing and thinking and just cant help but applaud myself for how strong i am. shit has happened to me and I am still here. not only just here but thriving. thats why i love eggun and orisha so much people, they rock my world and have helped me along so much tis amazing. santeria is amazing and i love my god bros and sis. i can't wait till the ocha to see ....lots. I look forward to my own actually. i just want to learn some dances and more songs get my money in a better place and do some more healing and then ill feel my ready but orisha know what i need and when so in the meantime i am learning to relax. you know i feel like i am babbling so imma go to sleep and hope tomorrow is tomorrow.
I just felt like I should say something...something

well, I am sitting here eating in and out for like the 2nd time this month and am thanking the gods for it plus a few other things. this week and this day have been rough but I have been sent my beautiful friends to deal. Roshan called, kristi emailed and nia is back in town and hopefully by the end of next week I would have seen them all. I ran to my hommie kristina and realized she rocks too. I guess I am finally in a good mood and it has been awhile since I have been in one like this. imma go to my madrina's b-day and set up a time to sit and talk about my warriors, my misa and whatnot. I think I am beginning to get excited about that and I am doing the spiritual work I thought I would not be able to do. it amazes me how much orisha has changed me in so little time and how far I have come. I am in love with orisha and they are in love with me. I love my eggun and they love me. I am held...next I feel that I need love and it is going to hit me when I least expect it. I know its comin and i think i am ready.
But i will tell you why on monday...

Uhhh there is more but I feel like keeping it private.
